This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a state representation learning method for robot control tasks using imitation learning. It also optimizes multiple models jointly, which is a common approach in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as the paper focuses on robot control tasks and aims to improve the performance of control systems. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes a method for learning abstract features of data, which is a common goal in AI research. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with control systems and their performance. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with visual data, but it does use observation reconstruction models, which can be related to computer vision tasks.
